OL,7,FThe guidance, published in September,
OL,8,Facknowledges corridor care is "not
OL,9,Facceptable and should not be
OL,10,Fconsidered as standard" but due to
OL,11,Fcurrent pressures some hospitals are
OL,12,F"using temporary escalation spaces
OL,13,Fmore regularly ` and this use is no
OL,14,Flonger 'in extremis'".
OL,16,FIt suggests how staff can deliver the
OL,17,F"safest, most effective and highest
OL,18,Fquality care possible" to patients in
OL,19,Fthese circumstances.
