OL,5,Cdoctors
OL,7,F"It violates the privacy of patients
OL,8,Fand leaves staff without access to
OL,9,Fessential, life-saving equipment.
OL,11,F"There are no circumstances under
OL,12,Fwhich it constitutes good, safe care.
OL,14,F"What once used to be an exceptional
OL,15,Fcircumstance, is now happening
OL,16,Fregularly in our hospitals.
OL,18,F"Health leaders and the secretary of
OL,19,Fstate must waste no time in
OL,20,Feradicating this shocking practice in
OL,21,Fthe interests of patients and staff."
